Besides the four Consensual contracts which are named in the text, certain praetorian and statutory conventions‚ though not denominated contracte, were enforceable by action. An example of praetorian pacts, or pacts enforced by the praetor, is constitutum or constituta pecunia, which we mentioned when treating of stipula· tion, as a form of consensual guaranty. An instance of statutory pact, or pact made valid by statute, is donatio inter vivos. It was irrevocable‚ and the donor could be forced by action to perform his ’ promise.
